{"id": 7488, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "3", "year": "2018", "session": "18N", "subtopic": "a-2-metals-and-inductively-coupled-plasma-(icp)-spectroscopy", "title": "18N.3.SL.TZ0.3", "topic_id": "a", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"specification\">\n<p>The presence of very small amounts of lead in calcium-based antacids can be determined using inductively coupled plasma-mass spectroscopy (ICP-MS).</p>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>State the type of particle present in the plasma formed.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[1]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>An unknown antacid sample has a lead ion concentration of 0.50 μg dm<sup>‒3</sup>.</p>\n<p>Calculate the concentration of lead ions in the sample in mol dm<sup>‒3</sup>.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[2]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>Electrolysis is used to obtain lead from Pb<sup>2+</sup> (aq) solution.</p>\n<p>Determine the time, in hours, required to produce 0.0500 mol lead using a current (<em>I</em>) of 1.34 A. Use section 2 of the data booklet and the equation, charge (<em>Q</em>) = current (<em>I</em>) × time (<em>t</em>, in seconds).</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[2]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>positive ions/cations/Pb<sup>2+</sup></p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>free electrons ✔</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>Accept “ions” <strong>OR</strong> “charged species/particle”.</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>[Pb<sup>2+</sup>] = 0.50 × 10<sup>‒6</sup>/5.0 × 10<sup>–7</sup> «g dm<sup>–3</sup>» ✔</p>\n<p>[Pb<sup>2+</sup>] «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\" = \\frac{{0.50 \\times {{10}^{ - 6}}\\,{\\text{g}}\\,{\\text{d}}{{\\text{m}}^{-3}}}}{{207.20\\,{\\text{g}}\\,{\\text{mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{-1}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0.50</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mn>10</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>6</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>g</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>d</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>m</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>3</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>207.20</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>g</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>mo</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>l</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>1</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>» = 2.4 × 10<sup>‒9</sup> «mol dm<sup>‒3</sup>» ✔</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>Award<strong> [2]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>«Faraday’s constant, <em>F</em> = 9.65 × 10<sup>4</sup> C mol<sup>‒1</sup> and 1 A = 1 C s<sup>–1</sup>»<br/>Q «= 0.0500 mol × 2 × 96500 C mol<sup>‒1</sup>» = 9650 «C» ✔</p>\n<p>t «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\" = \\frac{Q}{I} = \\frac{{9650\\,{\\text{C}}}}{{1.34\\,{\\text{C}}\\,{{\\text{s}}^{-1}}}} \\approx 7200\\,{\\text{s}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mi>Q</mi>\n<mi>I</mi>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>9650</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>C</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>1.34</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>C</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>s</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>1</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>≈</mo>\n<mn>7200</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>s</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</math></span> so <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{7200\\,{\\text{s}}}}{{60 \\times 60\\,{\\text{s}}\\,{{\\text{h}}^{-1}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>7200</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>s</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>60</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>60</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>s</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>h</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>1</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>» = 2.00 «hours» ✔</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">c.</div>\n</div>"}